    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "When I did this, I wanted to correct the issues with the rangeSlider from v1 which was not placing the middle pit at the correct middle.\r\n\r\nAnd also, to provide support for negatives values which was a nightmare for the v1.\r\n\r\nWhat I purpose, is to use the `precision` parameter to know at what decimal we should round for the start/middle/end pit value.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think?",
    "created_at": "2017-08-08T08:38:36Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2276#issuecomment-320890541",
    "id": 320890541,
